Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> You are in Eldergleam Sanctuary - just a small glimpse of what beauty Kynareth has to offer. Wonderful place, isn't it?
Yes, my friend. Though no one has been able to get close to her for as long as I can remember.

As you can see, Eldergleam's roots are large and stretch far, blocking any path to her trunk. | Though, believe it or not, there are rumors of a weapon that even Eldergleam herself would lift her roots for, more out of fear than respect.
Where can I find such a weapon?

G|Oh, I don't believe those rumors, my friend. Besides, who would ever want to harm such beauty? | Now, if you'll excuse me, I have nothing more to discuss. I encourage you to take your time and enjoy yourself. You look like you could use the rest.
Where can I find such a weapon?
Oh, I don't believe those rumors, my friend. Besides, who would ever want to harm such... Wait, it can't be.
[S] G|The rumors were true! You carry the one weapon Eldergleam fear - Nettlebane. I beg of you, don't harm the tree! Nothing good can come of it.
[S] G|The rumors were true... I beg of you, don't harm the tree! Nothing good can come of it.
<<Shared>> You are in Eldergleam Sanctuary - just a small glimpse of what beauty Kynareth has to offer. Wonderful place, isn't it?
G|You don't know what you're dealing with. There will be consequences if you harm that tree. Leave this place - you're not welcome here anymore.
